{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/terlan98"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/Contributors"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/terlan98"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"iOS Developer","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"role":"sampleCode","title":"Tarlan Ismayilsoy (2 notes)","roleHeading":"Contributors","images":[{"type":"card","identifier":"terlan98.jpeg"},{"type":"icon","identifier":"terlan98.jpeg"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Links","anchor":"Links","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"text":"Contributions","anchor":"Contributions","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Contributed 2 session notes in total. Their most active year was 2025."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"2025","anchor":"2025","type":"heading"},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-248-Explore-prompt-design-and-safety-for-ondevice-foundation-models","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-314-Get-ahead-with-quantumsecure-cryptography"],"style":"list","type":"links"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"kind":"article","references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-314-Get-ahead-with-quantumsecure-cryptography":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-314-get-ahead-with-quantumsecure-cryptography","title":"Get ahead with quantum-secure cryptography","role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to protect your app’s sensitive user data from the emerging threat of quantum computing, and safeguard user privacy. We’ll explore different quantum attacks, their impact on existing cryptographic protocols, and how to defend against them using quantum-secure cryptography. You’ll learn how to use quantum-secure TLS to secure network data, and use CryptoKit’s quantum-secure APIs for securing application data.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-314-Get-ahead-with-quantumsecure-cryptography"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/Contributors":{"abstract":[{"text":"WWDCNotes is only possible thanks to these awesome volunteers! Contribute now to get listed here as well.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/Contributors","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributors","kind":"article","images":[{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"Contributors.jpeg","type":"card"}],"role":"article","title":"Contributors"},"Contributors.jpeg":{"alt":null,"identifier":"Contributors.jpeg","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/Contributors.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","kind":"symbol","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes"},"terlan98.jpeg":{"alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/terlan98.jpeg"}],"identifier":"terlan98.jpeg"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-248-Explore-prompt-design-and-safety-for-ondevice-foundation-models":{"role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-248-Explore-prompt-design-and-safety-for-ondevice-foundation-models","type":"topic","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-248-explore-prompt-design-and-safety-for-ondevice-foundation-models","title":"Explore prompt design & safety for on-device foundation models","abstract":[{"text":"Design generative AI experiences that leverage the strengths of the Foundation Models framework. We’ll start by showing how to design prompts for the on-device large language model at the core of Apple Intelligence. Then, we’ll introduce key ideas around AI safety, and offer concrete strategies to make your generative AI features safe, reliable, and delightful.","type":"text"}]},"https://":{"identifier":"https:\/\/","url":"https:\/\/","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Blog","type":"text"}],"type":"link","title":"Blog"}}}